UserComments.Comment: Charged via Chademo twice, once on Friday 25th Sept (evening) and once one Sunday 27th Sept (evening).
Watch out for large pot hole on exit!
Pulled in to see an ENV200 charging. Busy charger!
Popular stopping point. Always busy meaning you often have to wait.
This is a busy charging point. There are so few in the near vicinity. You often have to wait.

We use this charger on a regular basis and wanted to comment that it has never failed us. On only one occasion could we not start a DC charge. However, this was due to the previous user ending their (AC) session incorrectly. A call to Electric Highway resolved the problem. It's an ideal location for many central belt journeys and, hopefully, Ecotricity can be encouraged to install a second unit!
Offline...again!!!....couldn't get home...kind people let me use their electricity to do a slow charge for an hour to get home....
